parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent failure of brakes can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and a higher risk of accidents, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
The repeated failure of headlights can reduce visibility, increase the risk of accidents, and lead to traffic citations, potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: being pulled over by law enforcement due to faulty headlights.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Harness Rusted due to Crack in Covering)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, including brakes and headlights, leading to reduced safety and increased risk of accidents.
The premature rust and corrosion of the frame can lead to structural failure, compromising the safety of the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: Excessive rust and corrosion on the frame
causing structural weakness and potentially leading to separation of the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the passenger.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag did not deploy during a crash
the passenger airbag is faulty or malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Latch Mounting Screw Failure (Mazda 6 only)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch mounting screws can cause the door to open unexpectedly while driving, increasing the risk of injury or ejection from the vehicle.
symptoms: The door latch is loose or faulty
the door opens unexpectedly while driving
the door latch mounting screws are broken or missing.
